df_dpf_col_asign_vw = df_input_dict['df_dpf_col_asign_vw']

import os
import pathlib
from zipfile import ZipFile
from datetime import datetime
from IPython import get_ipython
dbutils = get_ipython().user_ns["dbutils"]

s = '<<STEP_FILE_PATTERN_COMMON>>'
position = s.find('%')
run_id = <<PROCESS_RUN_KEY>>
PK = str(<<PROCESS_RUN_KEY>>)
files = dbutils.fs.ls('/mnt/<@@RAW_PATH@@>')

localpath = ""

for fi in files:
  filename = fi.name
  filepath = fi.path
  endwithzip = filename.endswith('.zip')

  if ((endwithzip) and (PK in filename)): # If input file is a ZIP file
    localpath = os.path.join("/dbfs/mnt/<@@RAW_PATH@@>", filename)


if position != -1:
  file_name = s[0:position] + f'*{run_id}*'
  file_name_for_zip = s[0:position]
else:
  s = s.replace('.txt','*')
  s = s.replace('.zip', '*')
  s = s.replace('.csv', '*')
  s = s.replace('.gz', '*')
  s = s.replace('.parquet', '*')
  s = s.replace('.xlsx', '*')
  position = s.find('*')
  file_name = s[0:position] + f'*{run_id}*'
  file_name_for_zip = s[0:position]
  

if ".zip" in localpath:
  df_input = spark.read.format('csv').option('header', True).option('delimiter', '|').load(f'/mnt/<@@RAW_PATH@@>/*{run_id}*/{file_name_for_zip}*')
else:
  df_input = spark.read.format('csv').option('header', True).option('delimiter', '|').load(f'/mnt/<@@RAW_PATH@@>{file_name}')

from pyspark.sql.functions import col

list_cols = ['MKT', 'FACT', 'PROD', 'market', 'fact', 'product', 'prod', 'mkt']

#df_dpf_col_asign_vw = df_dpf_col_asign_vw.filter("table_type IN ('FACT' , 'MKT' , 'PROD') ").filter(col('cntrt_id')==<<CNTRT_ID>>)

df_dpf_col_asign_vw = df_dpf_col_asign_vw.filter(col('cntrt_id')==<<CNTRT_ID>>).where(df_dpf_col_asign_vw['table_type'].rlike("|".join(["(" + column + ")" for column in list_cols])))
df_dpf_col_asign_vw = df_dpf_col_asign_vw.select("file_column_name","database_column_name")
df_dpf_col_asign_vw = df_dpf_col_asign_vw.distinct()

df_dpf_col_asign_vw.createOrReplaceTempView("col_asign")

df_dpf_col_asign_vw = spark.sql(''' select t.file_column_name, array_join(collect_list(t.database_column_name),',') as    
                                            database_column_name
                                     from (
                                        select file_column_name, database_column_name
                                        from col_asign
                                        order by file_column_name, database_column_name
                                     ) t
                                     group by t.file_column_name                             
                                 
                                 ''')

fact_dict = {row['file_column_name']: row['database_column_name'] 
               for row in df_dpf_col_asign_vw.collect()}

for key, value in fact_dict.items():
    if "," in value:
        lstValues = value.split(",")
        for v in lstValues:
            df_input = df_input.withColumn(v, col(key))
        df_input = df_input.drop(key)
    else:
        df_input = df_input.withColumnRenamed(key, value)

df_cols = df_input.columns
fct_cols = []
for item in fact_dict:
    if "," in fact_dict[item]:
        lstItems = fact_dict[item].split(",")
        for v in lstItems:
            fct_cols.append(v)
    else:
        fct_cols.append(fact_dict[item])
fct_cols = [n for n in fct_cols if len(n) != 0]

drop_cols = [col for col in df_cols if col not in fct_cols]  # to drop extra "columns" and have only user-mapped columns in the df
df_input = df_input.drop(*drop_cols)

lstDropRowCols = df_input.columns

ref_db_url = dbutils.secrets.get('tp_dpf2cdl', 'refDBjdbcURL')
refDBname = dbutils.secrets.get('tp_dpf2cdl', 'refDBname')
refDBuser = dbutils.secrets.get('tp_dpf2cdl', 'refDBuser')
refDBpwd = dbutils.secrets.get('tp_dpf2cdl', 'refDBpwd')

df_measr = spark.read.format("jdbc").option("driver", "org.postgresql.Driver").option("url", f"{ref_db_url}/{refDBname}").option("dbtable", "adwgp_mm.mm_measr_lkp_vw").option("user", f"{refDBuser}").option("password", f"{refDBpwd}").option("ssl", True).option("sslmode", "require").option("sslfactory","org.postgresql.ssl.NonValidatingFactory").load()

lstMeasrs = [row['measr_phys_name'] for row in df_measr.where('fact_type_code = "TP"').select('measr_phys_name').distinct().collect()]
drop_null_measr_cols = [col for col in lstDropRowCols if col in lstMeasrs]

df_input = df_input.dropna(subset=(drop_null_measr_cols), how='all')# to drop "rows" that have all measure columns null

for i in df_input.columns:
  df_input = df_input.withColumnRenamed(i, i.lower())

for f in files:
  flName = f.name
  endwithzip = flName.endswith('.zip')
  if ((not (endwithzip)) and (PK in flName)):
    folderName = flName

folder_files = dbutils.fs.ls(f'/mnt/{raw_file_path}/{folderName}/')

for f_files in folder_files:
  folderFileName = f_files.name
  if (fnmatch.fnmatch(folderFileName, common_pattern)):
    common_file_name = folderFileName
  else:
    common_file_name = file_name

cntrt_id = <<CNTRT_ID>>

cols = ['run_id','cntrt_id','rows_cnt','filename', 'comn_filename']
